{"slug":"intro-chains","graph":"both","title":"Three hops to anyone","sub":"Yen k-shortest intro routes to prospects, majors, funders — and actual humans","headline":"Anthropic, OpenAI, and Google DeepMind sit <strong>two hops</strong> from AoC — but every one of the 24 company routes opens through a rival, Gray Swan AI alone fronting 14 of them.","prose":{"intro":"<p>The landscape map shows who is adjacent to whom; this panel turns adjacency into asks. For eight company targets — the top nominated prospects, the majors, and the one top-shortlist VC that lives in the company graph — plus the top five funders, we compute the three cheapest intro routes each, then count which orgs and people keep showing up in the middle.</p>","how":"<p>Yen's k-shortest-paths is what a maps app does when you ask for alternatives: the best route, then the next-best that differs somewhere, and so on — never revisiting a node. We price each hop by social friction: asking along a business tie costs 1, a shared-investor tie 2, and a rival 10, so a route through one competitor must save ten partner hops to win. Three routes per target means two backups when a relationship goes cold. On the funding side the sources are the 3 grantees linked into the company graph that sit closest to AoC (Irregular, Apollo Research, METR), and hops are unweighted grant/investment edges. One structural fact matters: every person in the funding graph has exactly one edge, so no route can pass <em>through</em> a person — chains can only terminate at one, which is why the person routes end with a name and a role.</p>","method":"<p>Yen (1971) k-shortest loopless paths, k=3, via networkx <code>shortest_simple_paths</code> (Dijkstra subroutine on the weighted company graph; unweighted BFS hops on the funding graph). Edge weights business=1, shared-investor=2, competitor=10 are design choices, not measurements — reweighting reorders routes but cannot create reachability. For the 7 company pairs with two edge types we keep the cheaper. Targets were curated at bake time from the competitor-nominations and funder-shortlist panels plus the four majors; all 8 company targets sit inside AoC's 171-node component (0 unreachable), while 2 of 5 shortlist funders (Insight Partners, Google DeepMind) have no funding-graph path from any AoC-linked grantee. Funding caveats: 43/87 edges lack a year, and affiliation edges carry roles but no dollars.</p>"},"caveat":"Every company chain's first hop is a rival, necessarily: 4 of AoC's 5 edges are competitor ties, and the fifth — an unverified business tie to AIUC — is a dead end, since AIUC's only edge points back to AoC. Remove the competitor edges and AoC is cut off from the entire market (only the two-node AoC–AIUC islet remains). These routes exist because rivals see us, not because partners do yet.","inputs":{"companies":{"nodes":188,"edges":492},"funding":{"nodes":99,"edges":87}},"data":{"companyChains":[{"target":{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"},"why":"top nominated prospect","chains":[{"score":13,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"gray-swan-ai","label":"Gray Swan AI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"openai","label":"OpenAI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"competitor","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":13,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"haize-labs","label":"Haize Labs","graph":"companies"},{"id":"anthropic","label":"Anthropic","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"competitor","verified":false},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":13,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"gray-swan-ai","label":"Gray Swan AI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"anthropic","label":"Anthropic","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"competitor","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]}]},{"target":{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"},"why":"top nominated prospect","chains":[{"score":12,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"gray-swan-ai","label":"Gray Swan AI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"google-deepmind","label":"Google DeepMind","graph":"companies"},{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"competitor","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":12,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"irregular","label":"Irregular","graph":"companies"},{"id":"google-deepmind","label":"Google DeepMind","graph":"companies"},{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"competitor","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":13,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"gray-swan-ai","label":"Gray Swan AI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"openai","label":"OpenAI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"competitor","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]}]},{"target":{"id":"palantir","label":"Palantir","graph":"compani